<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[160,1156,402,877]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">
In their original description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vulcano M &amp; Pereira FS" box="[496,812,402,427]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" pagination="535 - 551" refId="ref20522" refString="Vulcano M A., Pereira FS. 1973. Duas novas especies do genero Scatonomus Er. 1835 (Col. scarabaeidae). Bol Zool Biol. 30 (30): 535 - 551. doi: 10.11606 /. 2526 - 3366. bzbm. 1973.121359." type="journal article" year="1973">Vulcano and Pereira (1973)</bibRefCitation>
described (and illustrated) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valois &amp; Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Vulcano and Pereira" baseAuthorityYear="1973" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Anomiopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lauropalui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">S. lauropalui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with three teeth on the apical third of the protibial edge, with all teeth directed forward. The authors used these characteristics to assign the new species to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Erichson" authorityYear="1835" box="[160,294,506,531]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,294,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">Scatonomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, after the examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[741,844,506,531]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">holotype</typeStatus>
, we agree that the protibial teeth are positioned at the apical half of the external edge, and only the apical tooth is directed forward. This finding means that this species belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Canhenho" authorityYear="2006" box="[911,1034,575,600]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Anomiopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[911,1034,575,600]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">Anomiopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
instead of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Erichson" authorityYear="1835" box="[160,294,610,635]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scatonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,294,610,635]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">Scatonomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, we propose the new combination 
<taxonomicName authority="(Vulcano and Pereira 1973)" authorityName="Valois &amp; Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Vulcano and Pereira" baseAuthorityYear="1973" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Anomiopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lauropalui">
<emphasis box="[811,1051,610,635]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">Anomiopus lauropalui</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vulcano M &amp; Pereira FS" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" pagination="535 - 551" refId="ref20522" refString="Vulcano M A., Pereira FS. 1973. Duas novas especies do genero Scatonomus Er. 1835 (Col. scarabaeidae). Bol Zool Biol. 30 (30): 535 - 551. doi: 10.11606 /. 2526 - 3366. bzbm. 1973.121359." type="journal article" year="1973">Vulcano and Pereira 1973</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Within 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Canhenho" authorityYear="2006" box="[444,567,644,669]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Anomiopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[444,567,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">Anomiopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species is easily distinguished from any other by two tufts of setae on the interocular space (
<bibRefCitation author="Vulcano M &amp; Pereira FS" box="[666,960,679,704]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" pagination="535 - 551" refId="ref20522" refString="Vulcano M A., Pereira FS. 1973. Duas novas especies do genero Scatonomus Er. 1835 (Col. scarabaeidae). Bol Zool Biol. 30 (30): 535 - 551. doi: 10.11606 /. 2526 - 3366. bzbm. 1973.121359." type="journal article" year="1973">Vulcano and Pereira 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[975,1032,679,704]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,508,531]" captionTargetBox="[166,1142,152,469]" captionTargetId="figure-400@6.[162,1152,142,476]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Terminology used to describe the head parts. (a) Scatonomus canhedoae sp. nov.; (b) S. chalybaeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5020907/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">Fig 2</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Canhedo VL" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" pagination="349 - 502" refId="ref19311" refString="Canhedo VL. 2006. Revisao taxonomica do genero Anomiopus Westwood, 1842 (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Scarabaeinae). Arq Zool. 37: 349 - 502. doi: 10.11606 /. 2176 - 7793. v 37 i 4 p 349 - 502." type="journal article" year="2006">Canhedo (2006)</bibRefCitation>
divided the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Canhenho" authorityYear="2006" box="[488,611,714,739]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Anomiopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[488,611,714,739]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">Anomiopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into three species groups, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valois &amp; Vaz-de-Mello &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Vulcano and Pereira" baseAuthorityYear="1973" box="[962,1101,714,739]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Anomiopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lauropalui">
<emphasis box="[962,1101,714,739]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110">A. lauropalui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
best fits the diagnosis of the group smaragdinus, in which the species can be arranged based mainly on the absence of a tooth transversely inserted on the dorso-lateral surface of metatibiae, and by having at least the first metatarsomere emarginate at the apex (
<bibRefCitation author="Canhedo VL" box="[166,331,852,877]" pageId="30" pageNumber="1110" pagination="349 - 502" refId="ref19311" refString="Canhedo VL. 2006. Revisao taxonomica do genero Anomiopus Westwood, 1842 (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Scarabaeinae). Arq Zool. 37: 349 - 502. doi: 10.11606 /. 2176 - 7793. v 37 i 4 p 349 - 502." type="journal article" year="2006">Canhedo 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
